
Overview

This module will install the PostgreSQL 9.1 server and client. It's been
tested on Ubuntu 12.04 LTS (Precise).


Example Use

Simply include this module in your node, that's it!

node 'my.node.com' {
  include postgresql
}


About PostgreSQL

PostgreSQL is an open source object-relational database system. With over
15 years of development it has a proven architecture and a reputation
for being powerful and reliable. It can support advanced features such
as HA, binary replication, JSON/XML explain plans, and key-value 
storage (HStore). Visit http://www.postgresql.org/about/ to learn more.




